It makes you realise how much the world will miss Christopher Hitchens. Speaking without notes (unlike Dr Dembski), incisive and clear thinking (ditto), unfailingly polite (ditto again), Hitch takes every point in the Creationist/Religious apologist canon and answers it to devastating effect. I can entirely understand why Prestonwood would not want anyone looking at this debate: they must have had students heading for the hills in droves!
